        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Actally while integrating some new functions for Zend_Locale I looked through the actual API and found that it needs a little bit tweaking...\n\nActually I am speaking of the localizing functions:\ngetLanguageDisplay\ngetScriptDisplay\ngetCalendarDisplay and so on \n\nI think for simplification it would be better to have them combined.\n\ngetDisplay($what, $detail, $locale)\ngetDisplay('country', 'AT', $locale);\n\ngetList($what, $locale);\ngetList('script', 'arab', $locale);\n\nThe following details and lists will be added :\nLanguage, Script, Country, Territory, Calendar, Timezone, Timezone_Short, Currency, Currency_Sign, Currency_Detail, Territory_Detail, Language_Detail\n\nInstead of 24 functions we will have only 2 functions which simplifies the API.\n\nThoughts, Opinion ??"
        },
