        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12911",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes it does reduce the number of functions, and it may help to reduce code duplication.  But then the developer must know which values are legal for the $what argument.\n\nAlso people who use code-completion tools may have an easier time understanding the explicit function names like getLanguageDisplay(), instead of getDisplay().\n\nAlso the unit tests give more assurance that we have tested all types of Display and List functions because code coverage tells us that we have tested each function.  If you combine the functions into 2 functions, then code coverage will only tell us that we have covered at least one type of display or list, not all of them.\n\nOne idea is that you can implement getDisplay() and getList() as you have described with a $what argument.  Then keep all the other functions but they are very simple:  they only call getDisplay() and getList() with the correct value for the $what argument.\n\nThose are some thoughts.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-23T13:48:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-23T13:48:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12912",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would only have the often called types with two seperated functions because I dont think that Timezone_Short names or Territory_Details are often called.\n\nSo we would have\n\ngetDisplay\ngetLanguageDisplay\ngetCountryDisplay\ngetCurrencyDisplay\ngetTerritoryDisplay\n\nand the related List functions. This is like with Zend_Date... the often used types like Time, Iso, Hour have an own function but Date_Medium or Hour_Short have not.\n\n\nAnd I also think that \"Display\" is not the right word...\n\n\"Name\" or \"Data\" is more related to what the functions does.\n\ngetLanguageData.... \nData seems to me better than Display.\n\nAlso some of these functions do not return display strings. This is why I think \"Data\" is more related.\n\nAdditionally when calling getData or getList without parameter a list of all useable parameters will be returned.\n\nThis are my additionally thoughts...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-23T14:15:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-23T14:15:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12935",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I had an discussion today in the zf channel.\nWe had come to the conclusion that we should change this function names to a more speaking one which is recognised also by non english people.\n\ngetTranslation\ngetTranslationList\n\nwould better say what this functions are doing.\nThen we would additionally have \n\ngetLanguageTranslation\ngetCountryTranslation\ngetScriptTranslation\ngetTerritoryTranslation\n\nand the related getxxxTranslationList functions.\nEven if the names of the functions are now longer, they do more say what they should return which is better for the user.\n\nI already implemented the List functions based on the old naming and adpoted the docu to reflect what information now can be used without the need of translating them.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-25T03:04:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-25T03:04:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13053",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved with SVN 3675.\n\nAlso unit tests and docu has been reworked \/ added.",
